    "created_at": "2015-06-18T17:16:51Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-18T17:16:51Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I agree, this points to a bug in to_csv. to_csv should quote special characters that occur within fields if to conform with the CSV standard. From RFC4180 documenting the CSV standard (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4180):\n\n```\n   6.  Fields containing line breaks (CRLF), double quotes, and commas*\n       should be enclosed in double-quotes.  For example:*\n\n       \"aaa\",\"b CRLF\n       bb\",\"ccc\" CRLF\n       zzz,yyy,xxx\n```\n"
  },
